Jenkins will:

1️⃣ Clone that repo 2️⃣ Build Docker image from it 3️⃣ Run container from that image

Build 1 → Pull Code

Name: dockerized-proj-builder Repo URL: https://github.com/swethaDharmaraj/my-nginx-app.git Branch: */main Execute Shell is optional Build 2 → Build Docker Image

Name: dockerized-proj-image

Build Trigger > Build after other projects built > dockerized-proj-builder > Trigger only if stable

Execute Shell:

cd $WORKSPACE docker build -t my-nginx-app . echo "Image built" Job 3 → Run Container

Name: dockerized-proj-run

Build Trigger: > Build after other projects built > dockerized-proj-image > Trigger only if stable

Execute Shell:

docker rm -f nginx-container || true docker run -d -p 8085:80 --name nginx-container my-nginx-app echo "Container running"

Only run: dockerized-proj-builder Check output: http://192.168.72.129:8085 I got an error: Docker Permission error, I resolved with the below

sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins sudo systemctl restart jenkins
